Chris/Mark, I am very familiar with the form and with the issues and I am happy with the contract, on the understanding that for any meters behind the LDC there is no "consumption/balancing risk" with the LDC - i.e. as it is a wholesale meter for a fixed volume, I am OK provided that if Domtar over/under consumes they are directly liable to the LDC for any balancing obligation.  There is also the issue of the a new charge "at" the Bruce Delivery Point which does not uniformly affect the market price for all market participants, but I understand that is a commercial risk Paul has accepted.  Peter.

